50|$|In 1988 he {{was elected}} to the Knesset on the Agudat Yisrael list. He was {{involved}} in the dirty trick in 1990, which resulted in him breaking away from the party to establish a new faction, Geulat Yisrael. He joined <b>Yitzhak</b> <b>Shamir's</b> government, and was appointed Deputy Minister of Health on 25 June. He lost his seat in the 1992 elections after the party failed to cross the electoral threshold. He later joined Likud and was placed thirty-fifth on the party's list for the 1996 elections, but failed to win a seat.|$|R
